If a username is entered or selected, then only entries from that user are shown. If the field is empty (default) or cleared (from keyboard or with the button on the right), all entries are shown.

Specifies the time of data displayed on the rest of the page (except the user filter and log prioirity limit), including which log entry or session is displayed at the top of the list, and location of session playback. Specific time can be entered from keyboard, selected with a date-time picker, or set to the time of the first, previous, next, or last entry. Updated as the log entries or sessions scroll by, and session playback position moves.
Specifies maximum priority of the log entries to display.
Appears when the log is scrolled past last loaded entry in either direction (i.e. may also appear at the top) and there are more entries being loaded.

Allows selecting any session available in the logs ("Sessions..." button), all sessions ("*" button), or a session among ones existing at the time currently selected with time transport controls (particular session buttons). Each particular session button shows the session ID, user name, rough location of time transport within the session, and whether the session playback is available.
Selecting a particular session using the buttons keeps the time transport the same, and shows the session at that time.

Particular session buttons appear and disappear as time transport moves in and out of particular sessions' time ranges, unless they are selected at that moment. If an out-of-range session button is deselected, it disappears (perhaps after a short timeout to allow for correction).
If there are too many sessions to fit on the screen at a particular time, the list is abbreviated with ellipsis or a similar indicator, and the "Sessions..." button
is expected to be used for selecting omitted sessions instead.

Log entries matching the user and priority filters. NOTE that the entries are displayed newest at the bottom as it matches the regular reading order, is less effort to comprehend, and will match session navigation and playback better.
The topmost displayed entry is the closest to the time transport position.

A brief information, playback and navigation panel for sessions with playback available. Displays basic session information, recorded terminal and allows moving time transport within session boundaries in various ways.

Playack also moves with time transport updates. If time transport is moved outside session boundaries by other means, slider remains at the corresponding extreme position, but changes shape to indicate the condition.
Reduced area for session-shaded log entries.

NOTE that since session playback updates the time transport, log entries move while session plays, is rewinded, or fast-forwarded. Vice versa, when log entries are scrolled, session playback position is relocated.
For performance reasons (since playback can be sped up, and/or there could be a lot of entries), entry list updates might be delayed.
NOTE that displayed log entry is updated during session recording playback, rewinding, and fast-forwarding, since that updates the time transport.
Updates might be delayed for performance reasons.

Session picker works similar to log entry list, obeys and updates the time transport, but if a session is picked, either from the main list, or the list of current sessions (including all sessions selected with the "*" button), the view switches back to the one the picker was invoked from, but with particular session (or none) selected.
The time in the time transport stays unchanged.
NOTE that the picker is also used on particular group, and user account pages. The former has the user filter limited to group members, and the latter has no user filter controls at all.
